Aug 26 2008 	Off the beaten path but worth it!	When we decided to go to Wrigley Field this summer for a Cubs game I found the Majestic through Trip Advisor and I'm so glad I did. While it was probably the smallest hotel room I've ever stayed in -- the Standard room made the hotel rooms in Europe look spacious by comparison -- the staff was so nice and the property kept up so well that we didn't mind. The neighborhood is fantastic -- residential, quiet, with interesting stores and restaurants -- and very easy to navigate. Despite being in Wrigleyville, which is north of Lincoln Park (a 10-15 minute walk to Wrigley), it's actually very easy to get downtown. I highly recommend the 145 and 146 express buses; you pick these up on Lake Shore Drive, a five-minute walk away, and they drop you in midtown in less than 20 minutes (be sure to get a transit pass from the front desk, they're not very expensive). It's a lovely ride along the lakefront. What a bargain! We wouldn't hesitate to recommend this to other baseball fans and look forward to staying there again -- maybe next season!	
